cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper deals with unsupervised defect segmentation on image data using convolutional autoencoders. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new loss function for the autoencoder, which involves examining inter-dependencies between local image regions, taking into account luminance, contrast, and structural information. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
